BFN 

  [Text] Lahij Governor brother 'Awad 'Abdallah Ba Matraf 
yesterday received the brother residents of al-Hutah, who 
expressed their happiness and jubilation with this meeting and 
welcomed the brother governor. They noted the service projects 
required by their city after normalcy has been restored, and 
after they have been rid of the iron fist, and domination of the 
criminal secessionist gangs once and for all. They reiterated 
their support for constitutional legitimacy, as well as their 
willingness to defend Yemeni unity, and cooperate with the 
governorate officials to implement the necessary projects in 
their governorate. 
  For his part, the brother governor affirmed that the state 
will strive to address the impact of the incidents caused by the 
secessionist and separatist elements. He added that the state 
is eager to implement all necessary and urgent projects. He 
noted that the governorate will witness the implementation of 
additional projects in the coming phase. 
  The brother Lahij governor visited several areas in the 
governorate, inquired about the well-being of the residents, and 
was briefed on the requirements and needs of the areas he 
visited. 

